description: The investment seeks investment results that correspond, before fees and expenses, to the price and yield performance of the Emles Protective Allocation Index. The index is designed to provide exposure to those publicly traded securities that can preserve capital and survive through a longer and more persistent economic downturn. In general, no less than 80% of the exposure in the index will be comprised of corporate credit securities and equity securities issued in the U.S. by U.S. companies and American Depository Receipts ("ADRs"), based on percentage of capital deployed (or exposure) in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
name: Emles Trust - Emles Protective Allocation ETF
